<H2>Environment Window</H2>
<P>The environment window allows you to see the detected environment
and module values
for the current packages and allows them to be overridden.</P>
The window shows:
<UL>
<LI>Override environment - Selecting this option allows you to override
the detected environment. When selected it enables the option buttons
beside the environment and modules listed below. Deselecting this option
will disable the buttons and reset them to the detected values.
</LI>
<LI>Environment - This lists the environment codes with their description.
An option button at the beginning of each line shows if the environment
has been detected (or overriden).
</LI>
<LI>Modules - This lists the modules. If they are detected on the current
machine part of the help text will also be shown.
An option button at the beginning of each line shows if the module
has been detected (or overriden).
</LI>
<LI>Cancel - Close the window without updating the environment/module settings.</LI>
<LI>OK - Update and save the environment/module settings.</LI>
</UL>

</BODY>
